On the first Thursday of June, July, and August, the Museum of Science teams up with local favorites Liars and Believers to present Yellow Bird in Space. A clownish maintenance crew finds a magical yellow bird, and a mad chase begins. Racing over land, across the sea, and into space � battling monsters, robots, climate change, and aliens � how far will our heroes go? Take a leap into a world of imagination, with masks, puppets, and gibberish. This adult clown adventure, adapted from the successful 2017 Liars and Believers production at the Boston Center for the Arts, is one small step for comedy; one giant step for� more comedy.

On the third Thursdays of June, July, and August, experience some of Boston's best live music in a way like never before � in the immersive world of the Planetarium. Each month a new live act will play a set of fan favorites � fusing together their music with innovative visuals created by the Planetarium team. These promise to be incredible one-night-only shows that you won't want to miss! One of New England's most exciting up-and-coming acts, Moe Pope and The Arcitype are STL GLD. The emcee/producer duo is heralded as one of the best live acts to come out of Boston and their sophomore album Torch Song was named 'Album of the Year' at the 2017 Boston Music Awards. STL GLD's momentum has continued into 2018, by starting the year touring with Ja Rule as well as being added to the Boston Calling spring line up alongside Eminem.

Using binaural technology Fox's show is not only an edgy, political, and personal journey, but an intimate ASMR experience intended to evoke physical sensations in the body.
Boston based artist Ruby Rose Fox is a cultural messenger of our turbulent modern times. Her music is as sonically compelling as it is subversive, packed with lyrics that reflect and challenge our current political state, from #metoo to the mass-shooting crisis.
